01:00.894 --> 01:05.332 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:05.365 --> 01:18.545 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Moments ago, House
Republicans
released their bill to meet a
key Trump campaign

01:18.578 --> 01:23.984 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
promise, to repeal and replace
the Affordable
Care Act, often called
Obamacare.

01:24.017 --> 01:28.622 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Some of the key changes include
ending direct
government subsidies for low-
and middle-income

01:28.655 --> 01:30.390 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Americans to buy coverage.

01:30.424 --> 01:34.661 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Instead, there will be
refundable tax credits
to do that.

01:34.695 --> 01:39.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Ending penalties of the
individual mandate,
and a phase-out of the expansion
of Medicaid

01:39.399 --> 01:44.871 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in 2020, but coverage would
continue for a
while for those already covered.

01:44.905 --> 01:48.642 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Lisa Desjardins just attended a
briefing in
the House Ways and Means
Committee.

01:48.675 --> 01:51.111 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
She joins me now from Capitol
Hill.

01:51.144 --> 01:56.450 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Lisa, some of these proposals
are not popular
among conservative Republicans,
are they?

01:56.483 --> 01:59.086 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: That's right,
in particular
the tax credits.

01:59.119 --> 02:03.290 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Some Republicans say that's just
another way
to giving subsidies to Americans
for their

02:03.323 --> 02:04.458 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
health care.

02:04.491 --> 02:07.227 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But the tax credits are a very
key component
here.

02:07.260 --> 02:13.633 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The way they would work, John,
is any individual
who makes $75,000 or less would
get some amount

02:13.667 --> 02:16.737 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of money to help them buy health
care, but
as a tax credit.

02:16.770 --> 02:18.638 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It would depend on how old you.

02:18.672 --> 02:22.142 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The largest tax credit would go
to those Americans
over 60.

02:22.175 --> 02:25.712 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They would get $4,000 to help to
go to the
health care.

02:25.746 --> 02:30.550 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Of course, on the other side,
Democrats say
this doesn't do enough to help
those populations

02:30.584 --> 02:33.353 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that can't afford health care
get where they
need to be.

02:33.387 --> 02:38.158 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: And the governors,
even some Republican
governors, who have used the
Obamacare to

02:38.191 --> 02:41.828 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
expand Medicaid, are they going
to be happy
with the phase-out of that
money?

02:41.862 --> 02:43.864 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: For a couple of
years, they
will be happy.

02:43.897 --> 02:48.135 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And then they will have some
problems in their
states potentially, depending on
how this

02:48.168 --> 02:50.037 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
works.

02:50.070 --> 02:54.875 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If you were on the Medicaid
expansion, those
are basically what they call
able-bodied workers,

02:54.908 --> 03:00.113 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
people who are under the poverty
threshold,
about 138 percent of poverty,
people who really

03:00.147 --> 03:04.851 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
can't afford health care
essentially, but
don't fall into other categories
of Medicaid.

03:04.885 --> 03:08.722 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Right now, you are able to
receive health
care through the Affordable Care
Act.

03:08.755 --> 03:13.160 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But you will be able to receive
that for the
rest of your life if you are
enrolled now.

03:13.193 --> 03:16.396 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You will be grandfathered into
this system.

03:16.430 --> 03:21.601 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
However, after 2020, there will
be no people
in that category allowed to
join.

03:21.635 --> 03:26.306 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, we're talking basically
working-age adults
who do not earn much money.

03:26.339 --> 03:28.041 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You can enroll now up until
2020.

03:28.075 --> 03:30.310 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You will not be able to enroll
in Medicaid
after that.

03:30.343 --> 03:35.282 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: All this, of course,
is if it passes
and if it passes in the current
form.

03:35.315 --> 03:40.654 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Sean Spicer at the White House
said the target
date for signing this bill would
be the Easter

03:40.687 --> 03:41.922 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
recess.

03:41.955 --> 03:42.923 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
How likely is that?

03:42.956 --> 03:44.591 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
How realistic is that, Lisa?

03:44.624 --> 03:47.828 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Well, we can
just look back
at the Affordable Care Act
itself.

03:47.861 --> 03:52.432 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It similarly had an early
summer, I believe,
goal date of being passed.

03:52.466 --> 03:54.201 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
When was it actually signed into
law?

03:54.234 --> 03:55.836 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The next year, 2020 (sic).

03:55.869 --> 03:58.472 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
So, that's an incredibly
ambitious goal, John.

03:58.505 --> 04:01.808 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The next couple of days will
tell us a lot
about whether that is even
doable.

04:01.842 --> 04:04.211 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We expect committees to start
poring over
the details.

04:04.244 --> 04:08.615 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, as you said, John, there
are disagreements
not just from Democrats, but
from Republicans

04:08.648 --> 04:10.417 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
about the details of this plan.

04:10.450 --> 04:14.588 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Lisa Desjardins, who
is going to
be busy following all those
details as they

04:14.621 --> 04:19.126 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
make their way through Capitol
Hill, Lisa,
thanks a lot.

04:19.159 --> 04:23.096 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the day's other lead story:
The government
is girding tonight for a new
legal battle

04:23.130 --> 04:26.066 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
on its second try at a travel
ban.

04:26.099 --> 04:30.403 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The new order, issued today,
again targets
a group of mostly Muslim
nations.

04:30.437 --> 04:34.908 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But it makes critical changes in
a bid to
try to avoid the issues that led
courts to

04:34.941 --> 04:36.276 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
block it.

04:36.309 --> 04:38.345 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Jeffrey Brown begins our
coverage.

04:38.378 --> 04:43.583 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: President Trump
signed the
original ban at the Pentagon
after just a

04:43.617 --> 04:45.519 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
week in office.

04:45.552 --> 04:49.756 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Today's signing was done in
private, with
only a single still photo
released.

04:49.789 --> 04:56.196 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It fell to Cabinet members to
make the announcement,
starting with Secretary of State
Rex Tillerson.

04:56.229 --> 04:60.000 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
REX TILLERSON, U.S. Secretary of
State: President
Trump is exercising his rightful
authority

05:00.033 --> 05:02.102 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to keep our people safe.

05:02.135 --> 05:08.141 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As threats to our security
continue to evolve
and change, common sense
dictates that we

05:08.175 --> 05:14.281 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
continually reevaluate and
reassess the systems
we rely upon to protect our
country.

05:14.314 --> 05:18.952 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Unlike the
original order,
this new one removes Iraq from
the original

05:18.985 --> 05:25.692 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
list of seven nations whose
citizens are barred
from entering the U.S., keeps
out Syrian refugees

05:25.725 --> 05:32.299 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
for 120 days, instead of
indefinitely, and
drops any explicit exception for
Christian

05:32.332 --> 05:36.836 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and other religious minorities
in Muslim nations.

05:36.870 --> 05:41.741 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In addition, it's made explicit
this time
that valid visa holders and
foreign nationals

05:41.775 --> 05:47.647 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
with green cards securing their
residence
in the U.S. are not included in
the ban.

05:47.681 --> 05:52.619 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The first order was effectively
halted by
federal courts within days of
being issued.

05:52.652 --> 05:58.058 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
White House Press Secretary Sean
Spicer said
today in an audio-only session
that it's now

05:58.091 --> 05:59.793 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
being revoked.

05:59.826 --> 06:02.696 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SEAN SPICER, White House Press
Secretary:
We continue to maintain that the
order was

06:02.729 --> 06:06.533 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
fully lawful, but there were
some legal hurdles
that we'd have to potentially
cross in terms

06:06.566 --> 06:08.602 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of enjoinment and things like
that.

06:08.635 --> 06:13.206 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, it was discussed with the
president Saturday,
and he made a decision that this
is how he

06:13.240 --> 06:15.075 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
wanted to proceed.

06:15.108 --> 06:18.645 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Among other
things, federal
judges said the original order
cited no evidence

06:18.678 --> 06:20.614 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of an actual threat.

06:20.647 --> 06:27.254 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The new directive says the FBI
is pursuing
300 terrorism-related
investigations of individuals

06:27.287 --> 06:32.425 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
admitted as refugees.

06:32.459 --> 06:37.163 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Officials also hope to avoid the
chaos at
airports when the original order
took effect,

06:37.197 --> 06:42.369 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
as people in transit were
detained, delayed
and expelled without notice.

06:42.402 --> 06:44.337 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Homeland Security Secretary John
Kelly:

06:44.371 --> 06:46.673 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN KELLY, U.S. Homeland
Security Secretary:
We are going to work closely to
implement

06:46.706 --> 06:52.512 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
and enforce it humanely,
respectfully, and
with professionalism, but we
will enforce

06:52.545 --> 06:54.180 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
the law.

06:54.214 --> 06:57.784 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
So, there should be no
surprises, whether
it's in the media or on Capitol
Hill.

06:57.817 --> 07:01.621 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: But opponents
showed no sign
of backing down.

07:01.655 --> 07:07.093 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Washington State Attorney
General Bob Ferguson,
who successfully challenged the
first order,

07:07.127 --> 07:08.995 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
spoke this afternoon in Seattle.

07:09.029 --> 07:11.164 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BOB FERGUSON, Washington State
Attorney General:
The chaos it inflicted around
our country,

07:11.197 --> 07:12.165 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
you all saw it.

07:12.198 --> 07:14.000 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
It wasn't right.

07:14.034 --> 07:17.470 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I certainly hope they take way
numerous lessons
from this experience, but, if
they don't,

07:17.504 --> 07:21.041 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
they can expect us to see us
challenging future
executive orders as well.

07:21.074 --> 07:25.445 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: For now, pending
court action,
the new order is set to take
effect March

07:25.478 --> 07:26.446 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
16.

07:26.479 --> 07:29.249 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm
Jeffrey Brown.

07:29.282 --> 07:34.220 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
