Trump may

19:13.986 --> 19:17.957 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
have information and
intelligence the rest
of us do not.

19:17.990 --> 19:23.195 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the Senate today, Democratic
Leader Chuck
Schumer said the claim added to
the need for

19:23.229 --> 19:27.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
an independent probe of alleged
ties between
Russia and the Trump campaign.

19:27.833 --> 19:29.635 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

19:29.668 --> 19:31.937 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHUCK SCHUMER (D-NY), Minority
Leader: The
events of this weekend, which
included another

19:31.971 --> 19:38.177 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
troubling, baseless tweet from
the president,
highlight and in fact strengthen
the argument

19:38.210 --> 19:41.847 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
for a special prosecutor to
conduct the investigation.

19:41.881 --> 19:46.919 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: The president sparked
the firestorm
with a weekend tweet: "Just
found out that

19:46.952 --> 19:51.557 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Obama had my wires tapped in
Trump Tower just
before the victory."

19:51.590 --> 19:57.797 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A spokesman for former President
Obama swiftly
denied it, as did his former
director of national

19:57.830 --> 19:59.598 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
intelligence, James Clapper.

19:59.632 --> 20:01.500 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JAMES CLAPPER, Former National
Intelligence
Director: There was no such
wiretap activity

20:01.534 --> 20:07.339 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
mounted against the president,
the president-elect
at the time or, as a candidate
or against

20:07.373 --> 20:09.208 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
his campaign.

20:09.241 --> 20:13.345 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Mr. Trump asked
Congress to investigate,
and Press Secretary Sean Spicer
said there

20:13.379 --> 20:15.381 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
would be no further comment.

20:15.414 --> 20:17.983 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Today, Spicer briefed reporters
off-camera.

20:18.017 --> 20:20.986 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SEAN SPICER, White House Press
Secretary:
There's no question that
something happened.

20:21.020 --> 20:24.924 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
The question is, is it
surveillance, is it
a wiretap or whatever?

20:24.957 --> 20:29.628 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But there's been enough
reporting that strongly
suggests that something
occurred.

20:29.662 --> 20:35.101 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: It appears to trace
back to Thursday
evening and conservative radio
host Mark Levin.

20:35.134 --> 20:38.404 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARK LEVIN, Conservative Radio
Host: Barack
Obama and his surrogates, who
were supporting

20:38.437 --> 20:43.375 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Hillary Clinton and their party,
the Democrat
Party, who were using the
instrumentalities

20:43.409 --> 20:49.715 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of the federal government,
intelligence activities,
to surveil members of the Trump
campaign!

20:49.748 --> 20:55.387 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: That was picked up
Friday morning
by Breitbart News, formerly run
by Trump adviser

20:55.421 --> 20:57.289 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Steve Bannon.

20:57.323 --> 21:00.960 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
President Trump's tweet came
about 24 hours
later.

21:00.993 --> 21:07.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
FBI Director James Comey
reportedly asked
the Justice Department to refute
the claim.

21:07.366 --> 21:11.971 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We dig in to the president's
claims now with
Congressman Adam Schiff, the top
Democrat

21:12.004 --> 21:16.942 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
on the House Intelligence
Committee, and Stewart
Baker, who was assistant
homeland security

21:16.976 --> 21:20.746 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
secretary for policy under
President George
W. Bush.

21:20.779 --> 21:26.685 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He also was general counsel at
the National
Security Agency from 1992 to
1994.

21:26.719 --> 21:28.854 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Gentlemen, thank you for being
with us.

21:28.888 --> 21:29.922 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Welcome to you both.

21:29.955 --> 21:32.258 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Mr. Schiff, my first question is
for you.

21:32.291 --> 21:37.696 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What's your response to the
president's request
that the Intelligence Committee
take this

21:37.730 --> 21:44.537 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
question, whether or not there
was any potentially
politically motivated
investigation, investigative

21:44.570 --> 21:50.743 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
branch powers were abused,
whether that happened,
into your investigation of ties
between Russia

21:50.776 --> 21:52.111 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and the Trump campaign?

21:52.144 --> 21:55.247 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And have you spoken to Chairman
Nunes about
this yet?

21:55.281 --> 21:57.016 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

21:57.049 --> 21:58.817 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ADAM SCHIFF (D), California: I
have not had
a chance to discuss it with the
chairman.

21:58.851 --> 22:03.656 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, look, I think this whole
allegation the
president has made is reckless,
and, given

22:03.689 --> 22:10.229 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that it comes without any
substantiation whatsoever,
breathtakingly reckless.

22:10.262 --> 22:15.601 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We already know from Director
Clapper that,
under the agencies that he was
overseeing

22:15.634 --> 22:20.739 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in the intelligence community,
there was no
FISA warrant directed at Mr.
Trump or his

22:20.773 --> 22:22.675 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
campaign.

22:22.708 --> 22:26.679 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, yes, we can bring him in
before our committee
and have him repeat in closed
session the

22:26.712 --> 22:28.547 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
same thing he said privately.

22:28.581 --> 22:33.185 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And if the reports are correct
that Director
Comey has said the same thing
and asked the

22:33.219 --> 22:38.757 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Department of Justice to push
back on this,
then it's clear there was no
criminal wiretap.

22:38.791 --> 22:41.227 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that is a simple matter to
resolve as
well.

22:41.260 --> 22:45.898 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I think the call for this to
be investigated
is much like the president's
call to investigate

22:45.931 --> 22:50.970 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
his claim that millions of
undocumented immigrants
voted.

22:51.003 --> 22:55.674 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's patently absurd and it's
designed, I
think, to give some patina of
respectability

22:55.708 --> 22:57.810 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to a claim that really has none
at all.

22:57.843 --> 23:00.946 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JOHN YANG: Mr. Baker,
breathtakingly reckless,
patently absurd?

23:00.980 --> 23:02.848 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
What do you say?

23:02.881 --> 23:04.650 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STEWART BAKER, Former General
Counsel, National
Security Agency: No, I don't
understand that.

23:04.683 --> 23:09.655 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We know from multiple reports,
including The
New York Times, that there were
intercepts

23:09.688 --> 23:16.362 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and there were FISA orders in
connection with
Russian efforts to influence the
campaign.

23:16.395 --> 23:23.969 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we know from Mike Flynn's
resignation
that those intercepts covered
conversations

23:24.003 --> 23:27.239 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that members of the campaign
had.

23:27.273 --> 23:32.278 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think it's perfectly
reasonable to say,
let's investigate that.

23:32.311 --> 23:39.818 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What we have heard from former
Obama administration
officials are very limited
non-denial denials.

23:39.852 --> 23:42.888 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That is to say, the president
says, I didn't
order anything.

23:42.921 --> 23:44.156 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Well, of course, he doesn't.

23:44.189 --> 23:47.026 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But the Justice Department and
the FISA court
could have.

23:47.059 --> 23:54.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have Jim Clapper saying, we
didn't target
the campaign or Mr. Trump.

23:54.433 --> 24:00.172 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There's a lot of other people
that could have
been targeted that would look
pretty political

24:00.205 --> 24:03.609 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
if it was done in bad faith.

24:03.642 --> 24:06.912 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think it's fair to ask the
question, what
are the facts?

24:06.945 --> 24:08.647 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And that's what your committee
is for.

24:08.681 --> 24:12.851 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Mr. Schiff, you say
that there
was no surveillance whatsoever
that might

24:12.885 --> 24:18.657 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
have captured some
communications between
people close to Mr. Trump?

24:18.691 --> 24:19.658 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

24:19.692 --> 24:21.493 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ADAM SCHIFF: No, that's not what
I have said.

24:21.527 --> 24:24.396 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think what Mr. Baker has
addressed is
really not what the president
tweeted, which

24:24.430 --> 24:28.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
was that the president had
wiretapped his
campaign.

24:28.167 --> 24:33.372 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's entirely possible -- and I
can't comment
on what we have been hearing in
the committee

24:33.405 --> 24:40.145 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
-- that, as part of our foreign
intelligence
gathering directed at foreign
spies, that

24:40.179 --> 24:46.318 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
we may have intercepted
communications between
Russian or between Russians and
Americans.

24:46.352 --> 24:53.459 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, frankly, if that's the
case, then the
president has a big problem,
because why would

24:53.492 --> 24:58.931 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Trump campaign people be talking
to the Russians,
if that was the context in which
communications

24:58.964 --> 25:00.733 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
were gathered?

25:00.766 --> 25:05.471 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So I'm not saying that's the
case, but if
what Mr. Baker is referring to
is our efforts

25:05.504 --> 25:11.643 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to target Russian targets,
that's something
very different than what the
president alleged.

25:11.677 --> 25:15.714 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think for a president of
the United
States to make this kind of an
allegation

25:15.748 --> 25:21.520 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
about his predecessor, I think,
in the eyes
of the rest of the world and our
own citizens,

25:21.553 --> 25:25.657 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
really brings discredit on
himself and on
our very democracy.

25:25.691 --> 25:29.828 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Mr. Baker, is there
anything nefarious
about that, if they were
targeting Russians

25:29.862 --> 25:34.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and they captured communications
with people
close to Trump in that process?

25:34.967 --> 25:38.804 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
STEWART BAKER: In my view, we
had to do that.

25:38.837 --> 25:41.907 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If the Russians are messing with
our elections,
we cannot tolerate that.

25:41.940 --> 25:45.344 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We need to know and we need to
take action
against it.

25:45.377 --> 25:55.921 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
At the same time, opening this
investigation
of one campaign, and in the
middle of an election,

25:55.954 --> 25:58.824 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
has enormous political
consequences.

25:58.857 --> 26:07.299 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And it's fair to ask the
question, were those
political consequences part of
the determination

26:07.332 --> 26:09.168 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to pursue this?

26:09.201 --> 26:12.671 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that is something that ought
to be looked
at, along with the Russian
attempt to influence

26:12.704 --> 26:14.473 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the election.

26:14.506 --> 26:16.475 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Mr. Schiff, is that a
legitimate
question for the committee to be
looking into?

26:16.508 --> 26:18.377 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

26:18.410 --> 26:20.679 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ADAM SCHIFF: Well, I think, if
you look at
the facts here, actually, much
of the criticism,

26:20.712 --> 26:25.117 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
frankly, that I have leveled and
others is
that the Obama administration
did too little

26:25.150 --> 26:30.622 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
during the course of the Russian
interference
in our election, not too much,
that the Obama

26:30.656 --> 26:35.227 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
administration, in fact, was so
wary about
being perceived as trying to put
its hand

26:35.260 --> 26:40.132 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
on the scales or interfere in
the election,
that they were reluctant to even
call out

26:40.165 --> 26:43.602 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Russia on what was so plain to
the intelligence
agencies.

26:43.635 --> 26:48.640 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Indeed, Senator Feinstein and I
had to take
the step of doing that ourselves
before the

26:48.674 --> 26:51.443 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
intelligence community was ready
or willing
to do that.

26:51.477 --> 26:56.048 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, I think, quite the contrary,
if the Obama
administration erred here -- and
I think they

26:56.081 --> 27:02.888 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
did -- it was in not calling
this out earlier,
not seeking sanctions along with
our allies

27:02.921 --> 27:04.823 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
earlier.

27:04.857 --> 27:08.760 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STEWART BAKER: I think you can
believe that
the president, President Obama,
wasn't sufficiently

27:08.794 --> 27:13.065 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
tough with the Russians and
still believe
that he was determined to be
aggressive with

27:13.098 --> 27:15.634 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the Trump campaign.

27:15.667 --> 27:18.704 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He does take domestic politics
very personally.

27:18.737 --> 27:26.144 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, you know, the FISA system
is set up to
provide protection for our civil
liberties

27:26.178 --> 27:32.851 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
by ensuring that the decision to
use FISA
is at the highest levels of
government, which

27:32.885 --> 27:35.787 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
it turns out, of course, are all
political
appointees.

27:35.821 --> 27:41.193 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And in the context of an
election investigation,
that's just not comforting.

27:41.226 --> 27:45.864 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I don't think that the president
is going
to be satisfied to hear, oh, no,
President

27:45.898 --> 27:48.534 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Obama didn't wiretap you, Sally
Yates did.

27:48.567 --> 27:50.702 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: I'm afraid we're
going to have
to leave it there.

27:50.736 --> 27:53.705 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Stewart Baker, Representative
Adam Schiff,
thank you very much for joining
us.

27:53.739 --> 28:00.712 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I'm sure we will be returning to
this topic
again.

28:00.746 --> 28:09.054 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
STEWART BAKER: It was a
pleasure.

28:09.087 --> 28:12.624 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JOHN YANG: Stay with us.

28:12.658 --> 28:17.095 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Coming up on the "NewsHour": we
talk to Jordan
Peele, the director of a horror
film about

28:17.129 --> 28:22.334 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
race; and students compete to
have their science
experiments sent to space.

28:22.367 --> 28:28.173 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, first, let's unpack the
